nwAppnMibRevText.name: nwAppnMibRevText
nwAppnMibRevText.description: Indicates the current revision level of the Cabletron APPN Router MIB in textual format.

nwAppnSysRouterId.name: nwAppnSysRouterId
nwAppnSysRouterId.description: Specifies the APPN Fully-Qualified Control Point name that is used to uniquely identify APPN Routing Services in an APPN network. The name format is NNNNNNNN.CCCCCCCC where NNNNNNNN is the network identifier and CCCCCCCC is the Control Point name. Valid characters to make up these two strings are uppercase letters A through Z, numerics 0 through 9, and the special characters $, @, and #. The first character of the string must NOT be numeric. Each string must be a maximum length of 8 characters with no embedded spaces and the strings are joined by a dot. nwAppnSysRouterId cannot be modified while APPN routing services is in any operational state other than DISABLED as reflected in nwAppnSysOperStatus. Otherwise, the request will be rejected.

nwAppnSysNodeType.name: nwAppnSysNodeType
nwAppnSysNodeType.description: Indicates the node type supported by APPN Routing Services which is always of type Network Node.

nwAppnSysCpAlias.name: nwAppnSysCpAlias
nwAppnSysCpAlias.description: Specifies the Control Point alias name used by APPN Routing Services.

nwAppnSysModeCosMap.name: nwAppnSysModeCosMap
nwAppnSysModeCosMap.description: Specifies whether mode to COS mapping is supported by APPN Routing Services.

nwAppnSysMdsSupport.name: nwAppnSysMdsSupport
nwAppnSysMdsSupport.description: Specifies whether Management Services supports Multiple Domain Support and Management Services capabilities.

nwAppnSysMaxLocates.name: nwAppnSysMaxLocates
nwAppnSysMaxLocates.description: Specifies maximum Number of locate requests that APPN Routing Services can concurrently process. Note: if nwAppnSysMaxLocates is set to a value too small, it will be internally increased to a higher value after APPN Routing Services has been successfully enabled. A subsequent GET operation on nwAppnSysMaxLocates will reflect this new value.

nwAppnSysDirCacheSize.name: nwAppnSysDirCacheSize
nwAppnSysDirCacheSize.description: Specifies number of located resources maintained in the Directory Cache. Note: if nwAppnSysDirCacheSize is set to a value too small, it will be internally increased to a higher value after APPN routing services has been successfully enabled. A subsequent GET operation on nwAppnSysDirCacheSize will reflect this new value.

nwAppnSysMaxDirEntries.name: nwAppnSysMaxDirEntries
nwAppnSysMaxDirEntries.description: Specifies maximum number of directory entries. If zero is selected, the number of entries is unlimited.

nwAppnSysLocateTimeout.name: nwAppnSysLocateTimeout
nwAppnSysLocateTimeout.description: Specifies time in seconds before a network search will timeout. Zero indicates that the search has no timeout.

nwAppnSysRegCds.name: nwAppnSysRegCds
nwAppnSysRegCds.description: Specifies whether the local or domain resources can be registered with the Central Directory Server.

nwAppnSysMdsSendQSize.name: nwAppnSysMdsSendQSize
nwAppnSysMdsSendQSize.description: Specifies size of the MDS send alert Queue.

nwAppnSysCosSize.name: nwAppnSysCosSize
nwAppnSysCosSize.description: Specifies maximum number of COS definitions maintained in the COS database weights cache. It determines the size of the COS Database weights cache. Note: if nwAppnSysCosSize is set to a value too small, it will be internally increased to a higher value after APPN Routing Services has been successfully enabled. A subsequent GET operation on nwAppnSysCosSize will reflect this new value.

nwAppnSysTreeSize.name: nwAppnSysTreeSize
nwAppnSysTreeSize.description: Specifies the number of routes maintained in the Topology Database routing tree cache. Note: if nwAppnSysTreeSize is set to a value too small, it will be internally increased to a higher value after APPN Routing Services has been successfully enabled. A subsequent GET operation on nwAppnSysTreeSize will reflect this new value.

nwAppnSysTreeUseLimit.name: nwAppnSysTreeUseLimit
nwAppnSysTreeUseLimit.description: Maximum number of times a cached tree will be used to compute a route before the tree is discarded and recomputed. This allows the APPN Routing Services to balance sessions among equal weight routes. A low value provides better load balancing at the expense of increased activation latency.

nwAppnSysMaxTdmNodes.name: nwAppnSysMaxTdmNodes
nwAppnSysMaxTdmNodes.description: Specifies maximum number of nodes that can be stored in the Topology Database. Zero means unlimited.

nwAppnSysMaxTdmTGs.name: nwAppnSysMaxTdmTGs
nwAppnSysMaxTdmTGs.description: Specifies maximum number of transmission groups that can be stored in Topology Database. Zero means unlimited.

nwAppnSysMaxIsrSessions.name: nwAppnSysMaxIsrSessions
nwAppnSysMaxIsrSessions.description: Specifies maximum number of intermediate routing sessions permitted by APPN Routing Services at one time. This must be a non-negative number.

nwAppnSysIsrUpperThresh.name: nwAppnSysIsrUpperThresh
nwAppnSysIsrUpperThresh.description: The thresholds control the congestion status of APPN routing services. If the number of ISR sessions exceeds the upper threshold, congestion status changes from uncongested to congested. When this occurs, the status will not become uncongested until the the number of ISR sessions fall below the lower threshold. The lower threshold should be less than the upper threshold to prevent thrashing. The upper threshold should be lower than nwAppnSysMaxIsrSessions. This must be a non-negative number.

nwAppnSysIsrLowerThresh.name: nwAppnSysIsrLowerThresh
nwAppnSysIsrLowerThresh.description: Specifes the number of ISR sessions at which congestion status will revert to uncongested. This must be a non-negative number. nwAppnSysIsrLowerThresh must be less than nwAppnSysIsrUpperThresh to prevent thrashing.

nwAppnSysIsrMaxRuSize.name: nwAppnSysIsrMaxRuSize
nwAppnSysIsrMaxRuSize.description: Specifies maximum RU size supported for intermediate sessions. Note: the number provided will be rounded up to the next valid RU size if necessary after APPN Routing Services has been successfully enabled. A subsequent GET operation on nwAppnSysMaxLocates will reflect this new value.

nwAppnSysIsrRcvPaceWind.name: nwAppnSysIsrRcvPaceWind
nwAppnSysIsrRcvPaceWind.description: Specifies suggested receive pacing window size for intermediate sessions. This value may be used as a fixed window size for fixed pacing, or as a tuning value for adaptive pacing.

nwAppnSysRtAddResist.name: nwAppnSysRtAddResist
nwAppnSysRtAddResist.description: Specifies a desirability factor for APPN Routing Services to perform intermediate session routing. 255 is least desirable and 0 is more desirable.

nwAppnSysStopType.name: nwAppnSysStopType
nwAppnSysStopType.description: Specifies the type of APPN Routing Services shutdown. Once specified, select disable from nwAppnSysAdminStatus. The shutdown choices are as follows: abort(1) All APPN Routing Services components are immediately stopped and resources released. To become active again, the APPN Routing Services must be enabled. immediate(2) APPN Routing Services immediately deactivates all links then performs abort(1) processing. quiesce(3) APPN Routing Services indicates to other APPN network nodes that it is quiesced. Session limits are reset on all modes, UNBINDs are issued on all endpoint sessions (CP-CP sessions last), and then immediate(2) processing is performed. quiesceIsr(4) Allows all intermediate sessions to end, then performs the quiesce(3) processing.

nwAppnSysBlockNum.name: nwAppnSysBlockNum
nwAppnSysBlockNum.description: This represents the 3 hexadecimal digit block number which precedes the 5 digit id number in the 8 digit node id used in XIDs and Alerts. The block number identifies the product type. Both the block number and id number combined, uniquely identify this instance of APPN Routing Services within the installation network.

nwAppnSysIdNum.name: nwAppnSysIdNum
nwAppnSysIdNum.description: This represents the 5 hexadecimal digit id number which follows the 3 digit block number in the 8 digit node id used in XIDs and Alerts. The id number uniquely identifies this instance of APPN Routing Services within a product type indicated by the block number. Both the block number and id number combined, uniquely identify this instance of APPN Routing Services within the installation network.

nwAppnSysLuTable.name: nwAppnSysLuTable
nwAppnSysLuTable.description: This table contains entries for LUs that are owned by adjacent LEN nodes. Defining or deleting an entry is equivalent to defining or deleting an entry in the directory database. To add an entry, set nwAppnSysLuControl to other. To delete an entry, set nwAppnSysLuControl to delete.

nwAppnSysLuEntry.name: nwAppnSysLuEntry
nwAppnSysLuEntry.description: Each entry defines an LU entry in the directory database. The fully qualified CP name and the name of the LU are the indexes into this table.

nwAppnSysCpName.name: nwAppnSysCpName
nwAppnSysCpName.description: Specifies the fully qualified name of the Control Point containing the LU being defined. The format of this name is NNNNNNNN.CCCCCCCC where NNNNNNNN is the network identifier and CCCCCCCC is the LU or Control Point name. Valid characters to make up these two strings are uppercase letters A through Z, numerics 0 through 9 and the special charcters $, @, and #. The first character of the name must NOT be numeric. Each string must be a maximum length of 8 characters with no embedded spaces and the strings are joined by a dot. This CP name must appear as an Adjacent CP in a link station definition where the adjacent CP type is EN and CP-CP session support is NO.

nwAppnSysLuName.name: nwAppnSysLuName
nwAppnSysLuName.description: Specifies the name of the LU being registered. The name format is LLLLLLLL where LLLLLLLL are the characters: uppercase letters A through Z, numerics 0 through 9, and the special characters $, @, and #. The first character of the name must NOT be numeric. The string must be a maximum length of 8 characters with no embedded spaces. Note that the nework identifier of the LU is taken from the fully qualified control point name of the adjacent LEN node (nwAppnSysCpName) which owns the LU.

nwAppnSysLuControl.name: nwAppnSysLuControl
nwAppnSysLuControl.description: Set this object to delete to remove an entry.

nwAppnSysAdminStatus.name: nwAppnSysAdminStatus
nwAppnSysAdminStatus.description: Sets the system-wide administrative state of APPN Routing Services. If enable(3) is selected, APPN Routing Services is activated. There are two cases: the very first activation, and activations subsequent to the successful first activation. Before activating APPN Routing Services the very first time, nwAppnSysRouterId in the System Configuration branch and all objects under nwAppnSysCfgLocalNode must be assigned a value. If not explicitly assigned, default values will be used for objects under nwAppnSysCfgLocalNode. After this first activation has completed successfully, all objects under nwAppnSysCfgLocalNode will be saved in non-volatile RAM and restored for the next node activation at power up time. After this subsequent power up, enable(3) may be selected without setting nwAppnSysRouterId or any objects under under nwAppnSysCfgLocalNode. Those values defined prior to the last power up or reset will be used. If disable(2) is selected, APPN Routing Services will become inactive in the manner specifed by nwAppnSysStopType. To modify objects under nwAppnSysCfgLocalNode, nwAppnSysAdminStatus must be disabled.

nwAppnSysOperStatus.name: nwAppnSysOperStatus
nwAppnSysOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating system-wide status of APPN Routing Services.

nwAppnSysAdminReset.name: nwAppnSysAdminReset
nwAppnSysAdminReset.description: Resets APPN Routing Services system-wide. Reset (2) forces a restart of APPN Routing Services without a graceful shutdown on any active router ports, without affecting any other routing services.

nwAppnSysOperationalTime.name: nwAppnSysOperationalTime
nwAppnSysOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAppnOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwAppnSysVersion.name: nwAppnSysVersion
nwAppnSysVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of APPN routing services in textual format.

nwAppnFwdCtrAdminStatus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrAdminStatus
nwAppnFwdCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the aggregate, system-wide, port Message Unit (MU) and byte counters. Enabled (3) causes these counters to become active. Disabled (2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwAppnFwdCtrReset.name: nwAppnFwdCtrReset
nwAppnFwdCtrReset.description: Resets the aggregate, system-wide port Message Unit (MU) and byte counters. Reset (2) resets the aggregate counters to 0. nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime
nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAppnFwdCtrAdminStatus has been in the current state.

nwAppnFwdCtrInMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrInMus
nwAppnFwdCtrInMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MU)s that have been received system-wide (for all ports) during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrOutMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrOutMus
nwAppnFwdCtrOutMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MU)s that have been transmitted system-wide (for all ports) during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrFwdMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrFwdMus
nwAppnFwdCtrFwdMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MU)s that have been forwarded system-wide (for all ports) during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrFilteredMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrFilteredMus
nwAppnFwdCtrFilteredMus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdCtrDiscardMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrDiscardMus
nwAppnFwdCtrDiscardMus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdCtrAddrErrMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrAddrErrMus
nwAppnFwdCtrAddrErrMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been received system-wide (for all ports), during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime, that contain an address error(s) in the SNA header.

nwAppnFwdCtrLenErrMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrLenErrMus
nwAppnFwdCtrLenErrMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been received system-wide (for all ports), during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime, that contain a length error.

nwAppnFwdCtrHdrErrMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHdrErrMus
nwAppnFwdCtrHdrErrMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been received system-wide (for all ports), during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime, that contain an SNA header error other than an address or length error.

nwAppnFwdCtrInBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrInBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrInBytes.description: Indicates number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been received system-wide (for all ports), during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrOutBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrOutBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been forwarded system-wide (for all ports), during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrFwdBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrFwdBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrFwdBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been forwarded system-wide (for all ports), during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrFilteredBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrFilteredBytes.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrDiscardBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrDiscardBytes.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdCtrHostInMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHostInMus
nwAppnFwdCtrHostInMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been delivered system-wide (for all ports), to local half sessions during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrHostOutMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHostOutMus
nwAppnFwdCtrHostOutMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been successfully sent from local half sessions system-wide (for all ports), to Path Control during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrHostDiscardMus.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHostDiscardMus
nwAppnFwdCtrHostDiscardMus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdCtrHostInBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHostInBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrHostInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been delivered system-wide (for all ports), to local half sessions during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrHostOutBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHostOutBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrHostOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been successfully sent from local half sessions system-wide (for all ports), to Path Control during nwAppnFwdCtrOperationalTime.

nwAppnFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes.name: nwAppnFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes
nwAppnFwdCtrHostDiscardBytes.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdIfTable.name: nwAppnFwdIfTable
nwAppnFwdIfTable.description: This table contains an entry for each router port which can be used by APPN Routing Services. This table is indexed by nwAppnFwdIfIndex, which indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex which identifes the router port for which an entry exists. These port configuration entries will be provided automatically based on physical port configuration. Such entries cannot be deleted - only modified.

nwAppnFwdIfEntry.name: nwAppnFwdIfEntry
nwAppnFwdIfEntry.description: Each entry specifies the APPN Routing Services port configuration for the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfIndex.name: nwAppnFwdIfIndex
nwAppnFwdIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfAdminStatus.name: nwAppnFwdIfAdminStatus
nwAppnFwdIfAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of an APPN Routing Services port for which the entry exists. enabled(3) causes the APPN Routing Services port to become active. disable(2) causes it to become inactive. There are various choices for the method by which the port can be disabled, which are enumerated by nwAppnExtIfStopType.

nwAppnFwdIfOperStatus.name: nwAppnFwdIfOperStatus
nwAppnFwdIfOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating condition of the APPN Routing Services port for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfOperationalTime.name: nwAppnFwdIfOperationalTime
nwAppnFwdIfOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAppnFwdIfOperStatus has been in the current state.

nwAppnFwdIfControl.name: nwAppnFwdIfControl
nwAppnFwdIfControl.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfMtu.name: nwAppnFwdIfMtu
nwAppnFwdIfMtu.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfForwarding.name: nwAppnFwdIfForwarding
nwAppnFwdIfForwarding.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfFrameType.name: nwAppnFwdIfFrameType
nwAppnFwdIfFrameType.description: Specifies the framing type for the APPN Routing Services port for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfAclIdentifier.name: nwAppnFwdIfAclIdentifier
nwAppnFwdIfAclIdentifier.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfAclStatus.name: nwAppnFwdIfAclStatus
nwAppnFwdIfAclStatus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfCacheControl.name: nwAppnFwdIfCacheControl
nwAppnFwdIfCacheControl.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfCacheEntries.name: nwAppnFwdIfCacheEntries
nwAppnFwdIfCacheEntries.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfCacheHits.name: nwAppnFwdIfCacheHits
nwAppnFwdIfCacheHits.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnFwdIfCacheMisses.name: nwAppnFwdIfCacheMisses
nwAppnFwdIfCacheMisses.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs. Setting this object has no effect.

nwAppnExtensionTable.name: nwAppnExtensionTable
nwAppnExtensionTable.description: This table contains additional APPN definitions for each physical port. Entries cannot be added to or deleted from this table. With the exception of nwAppnExtIfStopType, objects in this table may only be modified when nwAppnFwdIfAdminStatus is disabled. Note: if APPN Routing Services is not active, no entries will exist for this table.

nwAppnExtEntry.name: nwAppnExtEntry
nwAppnExtEntry.description: Each entry specifies additional APPN configuration parameters for the port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnExtIfIndex.name: nwAppnExtIfIndex
nwAppnExtIfIndex.description: Specifies the primary index into the APPN port extension table. This number corresponds to the index into the nwAppnFwdIfTable.

nwAppnExtIfPortName.name: nwAppnExtIfPortName
nwAppnExtIfPortName.description: Specifies the user friendly name for this port.

nwAppnExtIfPortType.name: nwAppnExtIfPortType
nwAppnExtIfPortType.description: Specifies the type of line used by the port. The value corresponds to one of the following: nonswitched(1), switched(2), or satf(3).

nwAppnExtIfDlcType.name: nwAppnExtIfDlcType
nwAppnExtIfDlcType.description: Specifies the type of DLC using the port.

nwAppnExtIfMaxRBtuSize.name: nwAppnExtIfMaxRBtuSize
nwAppnExtIfMaxRBtuSize.description: Specifies the maximum Message Unit (MU) size that can be received.

nwAppnExtIfTotLsActLim.name: nwAppnExtIfTotLsActLim
nwAppnExtIfTotLsActLim.description: Specifies the total number of links that can be active on this port. If nwAppnExtIfPortType = nonswitched(1) and nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole = negotiable(1), or secondary(3), then this value must be set to 1.

nwAppnExtIfInbLsActLim.name: nwAppnExtIfInbLsActLim
nwAppnExtIfInbLsActLim.description: Specifies the total number of inbound links that can be active on this port. If nwAppnExtIfPortType = nonswitched(1) and nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole = negotiable(1) or primary(2), then this value must be set to 0.

nwAppnExtIfOutbLsActLim.name: nwAppnExtIfOutbLsActLim
nwAppnExtIfOutbLsActLim.description: Specifies the total number of outbound links that can be active on this port. If nwAppnExtIfPortType = nonswitched(1) and nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole = negotiable(1), then this value must be set to 0. If nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole = primary(2), then this value must be set the same as nwAppnExtIfTotLsActLim.

nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole.name: nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole
nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole.description: Specifies the link station role - primary, secondary, or negotiable. For nwAppnExtIfPortType = satf(3), the link station role must be negotiable(1).

nwAppnExtIfActXidXchgLimit.name: nwAppnExtIfActXidXchgLimit
nwAppnExtIfActXidXchgLimit.description: Specifies the total number of activation XIDs that may be exchanged.

nwAppnExtIfNonActXidXchgLimit.name: nwAppnExtIfNonActXidXchgLimit
nwAppnExtIfNonActXidXchgLimit.description: Specifies the total number of non-activation XIDs that may be exchanged.

nwAppnExtIfLsXmitRcvCap.name: nwAppnExtIfLsXmitRcvCap
nwAppnExtIfLsXmitRcvCap.description: Specifies the link station's transmit/receive capability.

nwAppnExtIfMaxIfrmRcvd.name: nwAppnExtIfMaxIfrmRcvd
nwAppnExtIfMaxIfrmRcvd.description: Specifies the maximum number of I-frames received before an acknowledgment is sent to the sender.

nwAppnExtIfDfltTargetPacing.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltTargetPacing
nwAppnExtIfDfltTargetPacing.description: Specifies the pacing window size for BINDs on this transmission group.

nwAppnExtIfDfltMaxSBtuSize.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltMaxSBtuSize
nwAppnExtIfDfltMaxSBtuSize.description: Specifies the maximum Message Unit (MU) size which can be sent.

nwAppnExtIfDfltEffectCap.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltEffectCap
nwAppnExtIfDfltEffectCap.description: Specifies the default maximum kilo bits per second rate (line speed) for all links on this port.

nwAppnExtIfDfltConnectCost.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltConnectCost
nwAppnExtIfDfltConnectCost.description: Specifies the default cost per connect time for all link stations on this port. 0 is the lowest cost and 255 is the largest cost.

nwAppnExtIfDfltByteCost.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltByteCost
nwAppnExtIfDfltByteCost.description: Specifies the default Cost per Byte for link stations. 0 is the lowest cost and 255 is the largest cost.

nwAppnExtIfDfltSecurity.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltSecurity
nwAppnExtIfDfltSecurity.description: Specify one of the following security selections: non-secure - specifies no security. public switched - data flows over a public switched network. underground cable - data transmitted over a secure underground cable. secure conduit - line is secure conduit that is not guarded. guarded conduit - conduit that is protected against physical tapping. encrypted - encryption over the line. guarded radiation - line is proected against physical and radiation tapping.

nwAppnExtIfDfltPropDelay.name: nwAppnExtIfDfltPropDelay
nwAppnExtIfDfltPropDelay.description: Specifies the propagation delay which represents the relative time it takes for a signal to travel the length of the link in microseconds, with some of the more common default values enumerated. The default times in parentheses are in microseconds. These default values fall into the following ranges: minimum - no propagation delay negligible, lan - less than 480 microseconds terrestrial, telephone - between 480 and 49,512 microseconds packetswitched - between 49,512 and 245,760 microseconds long, satellite - more than 245760 microseconds. maximum - the maximum propagation delay.

nwAppnExtIfStopType.name: nwAppnExtIfStopType
nwAppnExtIfStopType.description: Specifies the type of shutdown for APPN Routing Services on the port. Once set, nwAppnFwdIfAdminStatus may be set to disable. The disable choices are as follows: immediate(1) causes the link stations belonging to the physical port to be disabled immediately without flushing pending messages and without initiating an orderly disconnect sequence. orderly(2) causes pending messages in link stations to be flushed, followed by an orderly disconnect sequence. The link station is then disabled.

nwAppnExtIfCpCpSupp.name: nwAppnExtIfCpCpSupp
nwAppnExtIfCpCpSupp.description: Specifies whether CP-CP sessions are permitted on dynamic links generated on this port.

nwAppnExtIfLimitedRsrc.name: nwAppnExtIfLimitedRsrc
nwAppnExtIfLimitedRsrc.description: Specifies whether dynamic links generated on this port are a limited resource. A limited resource link will be deactivated when there are no sessions using the link.

nwAppnExtIfAddress.name: nwAppnExtIfAddress
nwAppnExtIfAddress.description: Specifies the physical address of this port depending on the media type. For token ring or ethernet ports, the information is the 6 byte MAC address which starts in byte 1 and ends in byte 6. For token ring ports the MAC address must be specified in non- canonical format. For ethernet ports the MAC address must be specified in canonical format. For frame relay ports, there is no associated address, i.e., it will be a zero length octet string.

nwAppnExtIfSsap.name: nwAppnExtIfSsap
nwAppnExtIfSsap.description: For token ring or ethernet ports specifies the Source SAP Address of this port.

nwAppnIfCnPortTable.name: nwAppnIfCnPortTable
nwAppnIfCnPortTable.description: This table contains definitions for the Connection Network port table which defines which local ports can access a connection network. To add a row to the table, nwAppnIfCnPtFqName and nwAppnIfCnPtName are required entries. To delete a row, set the control field to delete. Adding the first row for a connection network implicitly creates the connection network and deleting the last remaining row for a connection network implicitly removes the connection network.

nwAppnIfCnPortEntry.name: nwAppnIfCnPortEntry
nwAppnIfCnPortEntry.description: Specifies the APPN Connection Network port definitions.

nwAppnIfCnPtFqName.name: nwAppnIfCnPtFqName
nwAppnIfCnPtFqName.description: Specifies the fully-qualified Name of the Virtual Routing Node. The name format is NNNNNNNN.CCCCCCCC where NNNNNNNN is the network identifier and CCCCCCCC is the Control Point name. Valid characters to make up these two strings are uppercase letters A through Z, numerics 0 through 9, and the special characters $, @, and #. The first character of the name must NOT be numeric. Each string must be a maximum length of 8 characters with no embedded spaces and the strings are joined by a dot.

nwAppnIfCnPtName.name: nwAppnIfCnPtName
nwAppnIfCnPtName.description: Specifies one of the ports which can access this Connection Network.

nwAppnIfCnPtControl.name: nwAppnIfCnPtControl
nwAppnIfCnPtControl.description: Set this object to delete to delete this port from this Connection Network.

nwAppnIfCnTgCharTable.name: nwAppnIfCnTgCharTable
nwAppnIfCnTgCharTable.description: This table contains the APPN definitions for a Connection Network's transmission group characteristics. Rows may be neither added nor deleted, only modified. Rows are added/deleted implicitly through CnPortTable.

nwAppnIfCnTgCharEntry.name: nwAppnIfCnTgCharEntry
nwAppnIfCnTgCharEntry.description: Specifies the APPN transmission group characteristics for the Connection Network.

nwAppnIfCnTgFqName.name: nwAppnIfCnTgFqName
nwAppnIfCnTgFqName.description: Specifies the fully-qualified Name of the Virtual Routing Node. The name format is NNNNNNNN.CCCCCCCC where NNNNNNNN is the network identifier and CCCCCCCC is the Control Point name. Valid characters to make up these two strings are uppercase letters A through Z, numerics 0 through 9, and the special characters #, $, and @. The first character of the name must NOT be numeric. Each string must be a maximum length of 8 characters with no embedded spaces and the strings are joined by a dot.

nwAppnIfCnTgEffectCap.name: nwAppnIfCnTgEffectCap
nwAppnIfCnTgEffectCap.description: Specifies the maximum kilo bits per second rate (link speed) for the connection network.

nwAppnIfCnTgConnectCost.name: nwAppnIfCnTgConnectCost
nwAppnIfCnTgConnectCost.description: Specifies the cost per connect time for the Connection Network. 0 is the lowest cost and 255 is the largest cost.

nwAppnIfCnTgByteCost.name: nwAppnIfCnTgByteCost
nwAppnIfCnTgByteCost.description: Specifies the cost per byte for the Connection Network. 0 is the lowest cost and 255 is the largest cost.

nwAppnIfCnTgSecurity.name: nwAppnIfCnTgSecurity
nwAppnIfCnTgSecurity.description: For the Connection Network, specify one of the following security selections: non-secure - specifies no security. public switched - data flows over a public switched network. underground cable - data transmitted over a secure underground cable. secure conduit - line is secure conduit that is not guarded. guarded conduit - conduit that is protected against physical tapping. encrypted - encryption over the line. guarded radiation - line is proected against physical and radiation tapping.

nwAppnIfCnTgPropDelay.name: nwAppnIfCnTgPropDelay
nwAppnIfCnTgPropDelay.description: Specifies the propagation delay which represents the time it takes for a signal to travel the length of the link in microseconds, with some of the more common default values enumerated. The default times in parentheses are in microseconds. These default values fall into the following ranges: minimum - no propagation delay negligible, lan - less than 480 microseconds terrestrial, telephone - between 480 and 49,512 microseconds packetswitched - between 49,512 and 245,760 microseconds long, satellite - more than 245760 microseconds. maximum - the maximum propagation delay.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrTable.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrTable
nwAppnFwdIfCtrTable.description: This table contains the Message Unit (MU) and byte counters for each port configured and enabled for APPN Routing Services.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrEntry.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrEntry
nwAppnFwdIfCtrEntry.description: Each entry indicates Message Units (MU) and byte counts on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrIfIndex.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrIfIndex
nwAppnFwdIfCtrIfIndex.description: Indicates the value of MIB 2 ifindex, which identifies the router port for which the entry exists. This is the primary index into the APPN per-port counter table.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrAdminStatus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrAdminStatus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the per-port Message Unit (MU) and byte counters on the router port for which the entry exists. enabled(3) causes these counters to become active. disabled(2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrReset.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrReset
nwAppnFwdIfCtrReset.description: Resets the per-port Message Unit (MU) and byte counters on the router port for which this entry exists. reset (2) resets the counters to 0. nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime
nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the amount of time in hundreths of a second that the per-port Message Unit (MU) and byte counters have been active on the APPN routing services port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrInMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrInMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrInMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MU)s that have been received, during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationaltime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrOutMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrOutMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrOutMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MU)s that have been transmitted, during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrFwdMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrFwdMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrFwdMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MU)s that have been forwarded during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrFilteredMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrFilteredMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrFilteredMus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrDiscardMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrDiscardMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrDiscardMus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrAddrErrMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrAddrErrMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrAddrErrMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that contain an address error in the SNA header that have been received during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrLenErrMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrLenErrMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrLenErrMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that contain a length error that have been received during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHdrErrMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHdrErrMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHdrErrMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that contain a header error other than an address or length error that have been received during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrInBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrInBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the Message Units (MU)s that have been received, during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrOutBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrOutBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in the Message Units (MU)s that have been transmitted, during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime, on the router port for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrFwdBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrFwdBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrFwdBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MU)s that have been forwarded during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrFilteredBytes.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrDiscardBytes.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostInMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostInMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostInMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been delivered to local half sessions during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostOutMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostOutMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostOutMus.description: Indicates the total number of Message Units (MUs) that have been successfully sent from local half sessions to Path Control during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostDiscardMus.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostDiscardMus
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostDiscardMus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostInBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostInBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostInBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been delivered to local half sessions during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostOutBytes.description: Indicates the total number of bytes in Message Units (MUs) that have been successfully sent from local half sessions to Path Control during nwAppnFwdIfCtrOperationalTime on the router port for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes.name: nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes
nwAppnFwdIfCtrHostDiscardBytes.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdLsTable.name: nwAppnFwdLsTable
nwAppnFwdLsTable.description: This table contains the configuration and management information for links to adjacent link stations. This table is indexed by nwAppnFwdLsName. Operations which apply are add, delete, modify, enable, and disable. To add a row to the table, the required fields in the row must be provided. The required fields are nwAppnFwdLsPortName and nwAppnFwdLsDestAddr. All other fields which are not provided will be defaulted. To enable a link select enable(3) from nwAppnFwdLsAdminStatus. To delete a row, set nwAppnFwdLsControl to delete(3). To disable a link set nwAppnFwdLsStopType and then select disable(2) in nwAppnFwdLsAdminStatus. If nwAppnFwdLsStopType is not selected, the link is disabled in an orderly fashion.

nwAppnFwdLsEntry.name: nwAppnFwdLsEntry
nwAppnFwdLsEntry.description: Specifies the configuration for a link to an adjacent link station for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdLsName.name: nwAppnFwdLsName
nwAppnFwdLsName.description: Specifies the primary index to the adjacent link station table (nwAppnFwdLsTable).

nwAppnFwdLsAdminStatus.name: nwAppnFwdLsAdminStatus
nwAppnFwdLsAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of a link to an adjacent link station. enabled(3) causes the link to become established. disable(2) causes the link to terminate. There are various severities of disabling a link which are selected via the leaf node nwAppnFwdLsStopType described further within this branch.

nwAppnFwdLsOperStatus.name: nwAppnFwdLsOperStatus
nwAppnFwdLsOperStatus.description: Specifies the current operating status of the link for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdLsOperationalTime.name: nwAppnFwdLsOperationalTime
nwAppnFwdLsOperationalTime.description: Specifies the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAppnFwdLsAdminStatus has been either enabled or DISABLED. If the operational state is pending-disable, nwAppnFwdLsOperationalTime indicates the amount of time since the state was enabled. If the operational state is pending-enable, nwAppnFwdLsOperationalTime indicates the amount of time since the state was DISABLED.

nwAppnFwdLsControl.name: nwAppnFwdLsControl
nwAppnFwdLsControl.description: Set this object to delete in order to delete the entry.

nwAppnFwdLsPortName.name: nwAppnFwdLsPortName
nwAppnFwdLsPortName.description: This link station port name corresponds to the port name index into the the nwAppnExtensionTable which describes the router port on which the adjacent link station is defined.

nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpName.name: nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpName
nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpName.description: Specifies the fully-qualified, 17 byte long, adjacent Control Point name. The name format is NNNNNNNN.CCCCCCCC where NNNNNNNN is the network identifier and CCCCCCCC is the Control Point name. Valid characters to make up these two strings are uppercase letters A through Z, numerics 0 through 9, and the special characters $, # and @. The first character of the name must NOT be numeric. Each string must be a maximum length of 8 characters with no embedded spaces and the strings are joined by a dot.

nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpType.name: nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpType
nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpType.description: Specifies the adjacent node type. The following values are valid: endnode(1), networknode(2). endnode(1) includes both End Node and LEN node types.

nwAppnFwdLsAutoActSupport.name: nwAppnFwdLsAutoActSupport
nwAppnFwdLsAutoActSupport.description: Specifies whether the link is automatically enabled when a session is activated over the link. It is an error to set this to yes(1) when nwAppnFwdLsCpCpSessSupp is set to yes(1).

nwAppnFwdLsLimitedRsrc.name: nwAppnFwdLsLimitedRsrc
nwAppnFwdLsLimitedRsrc.description: Specifies whether this link is to be deactivated when there are no sessions using the link. If nwAppnFwdLsCpCpSessSupp is yes, however, the link will not be deactivated if CP-CP sessions are terminated. Note also that a link over a non-switched port cannot be configured as a limited resource.

nwAppnFwdLsSscpSession.name: nwAppnFwdLsSscpSession
nwAppnFwdLsSscpSession.description: Requests a host system to initiate sessions between its SSCP and dependent LUs within APPN Routing Services. If set to yes, then nwAppnFwdLsPuName is required. Note: once this parameter is set along with other link station parameters associated with a link station definition, it cannot be modified. In order to change it, the link station definition itself must be deleted and then redefined with the new parameter.

nwAppnFwdLsPuName.name: nwAppnFwdLsPuName
nwAppnFwdLsPuName.description: Specifies the name of the local PU if nwAppnFwdLsSscpSession is set to yes. Valid characters are uppercase A through Z and numerics 0 through 9. The name must start with an alphabetic character. Note: once this parameter is set along with other link station parameters associated with a link station definition, it cannot be modified. In order to change it, the link station definition itself must be deleted and then redefined with the new parameter.

nwAppnFwdLsBackLvlLenEN.name: nwAppnFwdLsBackLvlLenEN
nwAppnFwdLsBackLvlLenEN.description: Specifies whether or not the adjacent node is a back level LEN Node. If so, specify the type of back level LEN node as follows: xid3(2) - supports XID-3 protocols, but does not include Network Name control vector in the XID. xid0(3) - Supports XID-0 protocols. Not valid if nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole is negotiable(1). noxid(4) - Does not support XID protocols. Valid only if nwAppnExtIfPortType is nonswitched(1) and not valid if nwAppnExtIfLocalLsRole is negotiable(1). If not no(1), then nwAppnFwdLsAdjCpName and nwAppnFwdLsIdNum must be specified.

nwAppnFwdLsCpCpSessSupp.name: nwAppnFwdLsCpCpSessSupp
nwAppnFwdLsCpCpSessSupp.description: Specifies whether this link supports CP to CP sessions.

nwAppnFwdLsEffectCap.name: nwAppnFwdLsEffectCap
nwAppnFwdLsEffectCap.description: Specifies th maximum kilo bits per second rate (link speed) for the link.

nwAppnFwdLsConnectCost.name: nwAppnFwdLsConnectCost
nwAppnFwdLsConnectCost.description: Specifies the cost per connect time for the link. Zero is the lowest cost and 255 is the largest cost.

nwAppnFwdLsByteCost.name: nwAppnFwdLsByteCost
nwAppnFwdLsByteCost.description: Specifies the cost per Byte for the link. Zero is the lowest cost and 255 is the largest cost.

nwAppnFwdLsSecurity.name: nwAppnFwdLsSecurity
nwAppnFwdLsSecurity.description: Security selections available for the link are as follows: non-secure - specifies no security. public switched - data flows over a public switched network. underground cable - data transmitted over a secure underground cable. secure conduit - line is secure conduit that is not guarded. guarded conduit - conduit that is protected against physical tapping. encrypted - encryption over the line. guarded radiation - line is proected against physical and radiation tapping.

nwAppnFwdLsPropDelay.name: nwAppnFwdLsPropDelay
nwAppnFwdLsPropDelay.description: Specifies the propagation delay which represents the relative time it takes for a signal to travel the length of the link in microseconds, with some of the more common default values enumerated. The default times in parentheses are in microseconds. These default values fall into the following ranges: minimum - no propagation delay negligible, lan - less than 480 microseconds terrestrial, telephone - between 480 and 49,512 microseconds packetswitched - between 49,512 and 245,760 microseconds long, satellite - more than 245760 microseconds. maximum - the maximum propagation delay.

nwAppnFwdLsTrgtPacingCount.name: nwAppnFwdLsTrgtPacingCount
nwAppnFwdLsTrgtPacingCount.description: Species the desired pacing window size for BINDs on this transmission group. The number is a value between 0 and 32767 and is significant only when fixed bind pacing is being used.

nwAppnFwdLsMaxSendBtu.name: nwAppnFwdLsMaxSendBtu
nwAppnFwdLsMaxSendBtu.description: Specifies maximum Message Unit (MU) size that can be sent.

nwAppnFwdLsNumActiveSession.name: nwAppnFwdLsNumActiveSession
nwAppnFwdLsNumActiveSession.description: Specifies total number of active sessions on this link. This includes both end point sessions and intermediate sessions.

nwAppnFwdLsdynamicLs.name: nwAppnFwdLsdynamicLs
nwAppnFwdLsdynamicLs.description: Specifies whether this link station was dynamically allocated (yes(1)) or whether the link station was defined by the user (no(2)).

nwAppnFwdLsStopType.name: nwAppnFwdLsStopType
nwAppnFwdLsStopType.description: Specifies the type of shutdown for a link. Once selected, set disable in nwAppnFwdIfAdminStatus. The shutdown choices are as follows: immediate(1) causes the link station to disconnect immediately without flushing remaining Message Unit (MU)s. orderly(2) causes the link station to disconnect after successfully flushing remaining Message Unit (MU)s.

nwAppnFwdLsPortNbr.name: nwAppnFwdLsPortNbr
nwAppnFwdLsPortNbr.description: This link station port number corresponds to the index into the nwAppnFwdIfTable and the nwAppnExtensionTable, which together describe the port used by APPN Routing Services.

nwAppnFwdLsDestAddr.name: nwAppnFwdLsDestAddr
nwAppnFwdLsDestAddr.description: Specifies the destination address of the adjacent link station depending on the media type. For token ring or ethernet ports, the information is the 6 byte Destination MAC Address which starts in byte 1 and ends in byte 6. For token ring ports, the MAC address must be specified in non-canonical format. For ethernet ports the MAC address must be specified in canonical format. For frame relay, the address is a non-null terminated string which is the ascii representation of the DLCI.

nwAppnFwdLsDsap.name: nwAppnFwdLsDsap
nwAppnFwdLsDsap.description: For a token ring or ethernet network, specifies the destination SAP address associated with the adjacent link station.

nwAppnFwdLsBlockNum.name: nwAppnFwdLsBlockNum
nwAppnFwdLsBlockNum.description: This represents the 3 hexadecimal digit block number which precedes the 5 digit id number in the 8 digit node id of the adjacent node. The node id is used in XIDs and Alerts. The block number identifies the product type. Both the block number and id number combined, uniquely identify the adjacent node within the installation network.

nwAppnFwdLsIdNum.name: nwAppnFwdLsIdNum
nwAppnFwdLsIdNum.description: This represents the 5 hexadecimal digit id number which follows the 3 digit block number in the 8 digit node id of the adjacent node. The node id is used in XIDs and Alerts. The id number uniquely identifies the adjacent node within a product type indicated by its block number. Both the block number and id number combined, uniquely identify the adjacent node within the installation network.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrTable.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrTable
nwAppnFwdLsCtrTable.description: This table contains the Basic Link Unit (BLU) and byte counters for each configured adjacent link station.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrEntry.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrEntry
nwAppnFwdLsCtrEntry.description: Each entry indicates the Basic Link Unit (BLU) and byte count for the configured adjacent link station for which the entry exists.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrLsName.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrLsName
nwAppnFwdLsCtrLsName.description: Specifies the primary index into the link station counter table. This index is the link station name.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrAdminStatus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrAdminStatus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrAdminStatus.description: Sets the administrative state of the Basic Link Unit (BLU) and byte counters on the link for which this entry exists. enabled(3) causes these counters to reset and become active. disabled(2) causes these counters to become inactive.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrReset.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrReset
nwAppnFwdLsCtrReset.description: Resets the Basic Link Unit (BLU) and byte counters on the link for which this entry exists. reset(2) resets the counters to 0. nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime is also reset to 0.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime
nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime.description: Specifies the amount of time in hundreths of a second that the Basic Link Unit (BLU) and byte counters have been active on the link for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrInBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrInBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrInBlus.description: Specifies the total number of Basic Link Unit (BLU)s that have been received, during nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationaltime, on the link for which this entry exists. This includes both information (I-frame) and XID BLUs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrOutBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrOutBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrOutBlus.description: Specifies the total number of Basic Link Unit (BLU)s that have been transmitted, during nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime, on the link for which this entry exists. This includes both information (I-frame) and XID BLUs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrFwdBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrFwdBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrFwdBlus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrFilteredBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrFilteredBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrFilteredBlus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrDiscardBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrDiscardBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrDiscardBlus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrAddrErrBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrAddrErrBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrAddrErrBlus.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrLenErrBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrLenErrBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrLenErrBlus.description: Specifies the total number of received Basic Link Unit (BLU)s during nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime which have invalid DLC headers on the link for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrHdrErrBlus.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrHdrErrBlus
nwAppnFwdLsCtrHdrErrBlus.description: Specifies the total number of received Basic Link Unit (BLU)s during nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime which have length errors on the link for which this entry exists.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrInBytes.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrInBytes
nwAppnFwdLsCtrInBytes.description: Specifies the total number of bytes that have been received, during nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime, on the link for which the entry exists. This includes bytes contained in information (I-frames) and XID BLUs.

nwAppnFwdLsCtrOutBytes.name: nwAppnFwdLsCtrOutBytes
nwAppnFwdLsCtrOutBytes.description: Specifies the total number of bytes that have been transmitted, during nwAppnFwdLsCtrOperationalTime, on the link for which the entry exists. This includes bytes contained in information (I-frames) and XID BLUs.

nwAppnIsrAdminStatus.name: nwAppnIsrAdminStatus
nwAppnIsrAdminStatus.description: Intermediate Session Routing cannot be turned on and off. Any modifications to this leaf will have no affect.

nwAppnIsrOperStatus.name: nwAppnIsrOperStatus
nwAppnIsrOperStatus.description: Specifies the current operating condition of the ISR routing protocol, system-wide.

nwAppnIsrAdminReset.name: nwAppnIsrAdminReset
nwAppnIsrAdminReset.description: This object does not apply to this protocol. It is a common object, inherited from the MIB framework used to provide a common management interface to all the Cabletron Routing Services protocol-specific MIBs.

nwAppnIsrOperationalTime.name: nwAppnIsrOperationalTime
nwAppnIsrOperationalTime.description: Indicates the elapsed time, in hundredths of a second, that nwAppnOperStatus has been in its current state.

nwAppnIsrVersion.name: nwAppnIsrVersion
nwAppnIsrVersion.description: Indicates the current revision level of the ISR firmware in textual format. This is the same version number as that of APPN Routing Services firmware, nwAppnSysVersion.

nwAppnEventAdminStatus.name: nwAppnEventAdminStatus
nwAppnEventAdminStatus.description: Set the administrative state of APPN Routing Services event logging. enabled(3) causes the event log to become active. disabled(2) causes the event log to become inactive.

nwAppnEventMaxEntries.name: nwAppnEventMaxEntries
nwAppnEventMaxEntries.description: Sets the maximum number of entries allowed in the event log table. When the number of entries reaches the value of nwAppnEventMaxEntries the first (oldest) entry is deleted to allow a new entry to be added.

nwAppnEventTraceAll.name: nwAppnEventTraceAll
nwAppnEventTraceAll.description: enabled(3) allows logging of all event types on all ports. disabled(2) causes the filter table to specify which events to log.

nwAppnEventFilterTable.name: nwAppnEventFilterTable
nwAppnEventFilterTable.description: This table contains descriptions of how to filter log entries.

nwAppnEventFilterEntry.name: nwAppnEventFilterEntry
nwAppnEventFilterEntry.description: Each entry specifies the filter for log entries. The instance nwAppnEventProtocol refers to the instance used in the nwRtgProtocolTable and nwComponentTable specified by the ctrouter-mib.txt.

nwAppnEventFltrProtocol.name: nwAppnEventFltrProtocol
nwAppnEventFltrProtocol.description: Selects the protocol to log events from.

nwAppnEventFltrIfNum.name: nwAppnEventFltrIfNum
nwAppnEventFltrIfNum.description: Specifies the APPN Routing Services port on which to log events.

nwAppnEventFltrControl.name: nwAppnEventFltrControl
nwAppnEventFltrControl.description: Setting this field to delete will allow entries to be removed from the table. This is done by adding new entries with instance fields that match the entry to be removed from the table. The new entry being added must have this control field set to delete in order for the matching entry already in the table to be deleted. Setting this field to add will add the entry to the table.

nwAppnEventFltrType.name: nwAppnEventFltrType
nwAppnEventFltrType.description: This bit field mask filter will allow only events of certain types to be logged. By default all types will be logged. Clearing event types from this field will cause those types not to be logged. Adding event types to this field will enable those types to be logged.

nwAppnEventFltrSeverity.name: nwAppnEventFltrSeverity
nwAppnEventFltrSeverity.description: This filter controls the amount of logging by ignoring events of lower priority than that specified by the filter value. Specifying highest(1) causes all events except those of highest severity to be ignored. Specifying highmed(2) causes lowest severity events to be ignored. Specifying highlow(3) causes all events to be logged. highmed(2) is the default setting.

nwAppnEventFltrAction.name: nwAppnEventFltrAction
nwAppnEventFltrAction.description: This field specifies how the events are to be logged. Specifying log(1) stores the events in the event log table (defined below). Specifying trap(2) sends events out through the trap mechanism. Specifying logTrap(3) does both.

nwAppnEventTable.name: nwAppnEventTable
nwAppnEventTable.description: This table contains all events that have been logged.

nwAppnEventEntry.name: nwAppnEventEntry
nwAppnEventEntry.description: Each entry specifies events that have been logged.

nwAppnEventNumber.name: nwAppnEventNumber
nwAppnEventNumber.description: This ordinal number uniquely identifies events.

nwAppnEventTime.name: nwAppnEventTime
nwAppnEventTime.description: This number specifies when the event was logged.

nwAppnEventSeverity.name: nwAppnEventSeverity
nwAppnEventSeverity.description: Specifies the severity of the event logged.

nwAppnEventProtocol.name: nwAppnEventProtocol
nwAppnEventProtocol.description: Specifies the protocol where the event occured.

nwAppnEventIfNum.name: nwAppnEventIfNum
nwAppnEventIfNum.description: Specifies the APPN Routing Services port the event occurred on.

nwAppnEventTextString.name: nwAppnEventTextString
nwAppnEventTextString.description: Specifies the actual text string to be logged.
